{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1733,"text":"Father Daniel Berrigan once said\nthat \"writing about prisoners"},{"time":4921,"text":"is a little like writing about the dead.\""},{"time":7720,"text":"I think what he meant is that\nwe treat prisoners as ghosts."},{"time":10934,"text":"They're unseen and unheard."},{"time":13681,"text":"It's easy to simply ignore them"},{"time":15341,"text":"and it's even easier when the government\ngoes to great lengths to keep them hidden."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19754,"text":"As a journalist, I think these stories"},{"time":21993,"text":"of what people in power do\nwhen no one is watching,"},{"time":25065,"text":"are precisely the stories\nthat we need to tell."},{"time":28058,"text":"That's why I began investigating"},{"time":29621,"text":"the most secretive and experimental\nprison units in the United States,"},{"time":33432,"text":"for so-called \"second-tier\" terrorists."},{"time":37322,"text":"The government calls these units\nCommunications Management Units or CMUs."},{"time":42858,"text":"Prisoners and guards call them\n\"Little Guantanamo.\""},{"time":46886,"text":"They are islands unto themselves."},{"time":49203,"text":"But unlike Gitmo they exist\nright here, at home,"},{"time":53574,"text":"floating within larger federal prisons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57305,"text":"There are 2 CMUs."},{"time":58953,"text":"One was opened inside the prison\nin Terre Haute, Indiana,"},{"time":62097,"text":"and the other is inside this prison,\nin Marion, Illinois."},{"time":66669,"text":"Neither of them underwent\nthe formal review process"},{"time":69118,"text":"that is required by law\nwhen they were opened."},{"time":73232,"text":"CMU prisoners have all\nbeen convicted of crimes."},{"time":76053,"text":"Some of their cases are questionable\nand some involve threats and violence."},{"time":81110,"text":"I'm not here to argue the guilt\nor innocence of any prisoner."},{"time":84388,"text":"I'm here because as Supreme Court Justice\nThurgood Marshall said,"},{"time":87947,"text":"\"When the prisons and gates slam shut,"},{"time":90428,"text":"prisoners do not lose\ntheir human quality.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":94515,"text":"Every prisoner I've interviewed\nhas said there are three flecks of light"},{"time":99206,"text":"in the darkness of prison:"},{"time":101664,"text":"phone calls,"},{"time":102886,"text":"letters"},{"time":104061,"text":"and visits from family."},{"time":106166,"text":"CMUs aren't solitary confinement,\nbut they radically restrict all of these"},{"time":110093,"text":"to levels that meet or exceed the most\nextreme prisons in the United States."},{"time":114496,"text":"Their phone calls can be limited\nto 45 minutes a month,"},{"time":117801,"text":"compared to the 300 minutes\nother prisoners receive."},{"time":122345,"text":"Their letters can be limited\nto six pieces of paper."},{"time":125516,"text":"Their visits can be limited\nto four hours per month,"},{"time":127971,"text":"compared to the 35 hours that people\nlike Olympic Park bomber Eric Rudolph"},{"time":133701,"text":"receive in the supermax."},{"time":136215,"text":"On top of that, CMU visits are non-contact\nwhich means prisoners are not allowed"},{"time":141227,"text":"to even hug their family."},{"time":144093,"text":"As one CMU prisoner said,"},{"time":146043,"text":"\"We're not being tortured here,\nexcept psychologically.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":150893,"text":"The government won't say\nwho is imprisoned here."},{"time":153750,"text":"But through court documents,\nopen records requests"},{"time":157401,"text":"and interviews with current\nand former prisoners,"},{"time":159983,"text":"some small windows\ninto the CMUs have opened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164005,"text":"There's an estimated\n60 to 70 prisoners here,"},{"time":167111,"text":"and they're overwhelmingly Muslim."},{"time":169825,"text":"They include people like Dr. Rafil Dhafir,"},{"time":173017,"text":"who violated the economic sanctions\non Iraq by sending medical supplies"},{"time":177065,"text":"for the children there."},{"time":179967,"text":"They've included people like Yassin Aref."},{"time":182892,"text":"Aref and his family fled to New York\nfrom Saddam Hussein's Iraq as refugees."},{"time":188094,"text":"He was arrested in 2004\nas part of an FBI sting."},{"time":192784,"text":"Aref is an imam and he was asked\nto bear witness to a loan,"},{"time":196282,"text":"which is a tradition in Islamic culture."},{"time":198703,"text":"It turned out that one of the people\ninvolved in the loan was trying to enlist"},{"time":202543,"text":"someone else in a fake attack."},{"time":205452,"text":"Aref didn't know."},{"time":207561,"text":"For that, he was convicted"},{"time":208855,"text":"of conspiracy to provide material support\nto a terrorist group."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214309,"text":"The CMUs also include\nsome non-Muslim prisoners."},{"time":217563,"text":"The guards call them \"balancers,\""},{"time":220390,"text":"meaning they help balance out\nthe racial numbers,"},{"time":223278,"text":"in hopes of deflecting law suits."},{"time":226223,"text":"These balancers include animal rights\nand environmental activists"},{"time":229889,"text":"like Daniel McGowan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231643,"text":"McGowan was convicted\nof participating in two arsons"},{"time":234453,"text":"in the name of defending the environment"},{"time":236589,"text":"as part of the Earth Liberation Front."},{"time":239690,"text":"During his sentencing, he was afraid\nthat he would be sent"},{"time":242462,"text":"to a rumored secret prison for terrorists."},{"time":245560,"text":"The judge dismissed all those fears,"},{"time":247448,"text":"saying that they\nweren't supported by any facts."},{"time":250606,"text":"But that might be because the government\nhasn't fully explained"},{"time":253885,"text":"why some prisoners end up in a CMU,"},{"time":256311,"text":"and who is responsible\nfor these decisions."},{"time":260142,"text":"When McGowan was transferred, he was told"},{"time":262201,"text":"it's because he is a \"domestic terrorist,\""},{"time":265627,"text":"a term the FBI uses repeatedly when\ntalking about environmental activists."},{"time":270978,"text":"Now, keep in mind there are about 400\nprisoners in US prisons"},{"time":274773,"text":"who are classified as terrorists,"},{"time":276560,"text":"and only a handful of them\nare in the CMUs."},{"time":279169,"text":"In McGowan's case, he was previously\nat a low-security prison"},{"time":282816,"text":"and he had no communications violations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287354,"text":"So, why was he moved?"},{"time":290173,"text":"Like other CMU prisoners,"},{"time":291534,"text":"McGowan repeatedly asked\nfor an answer, a hearing,"},{"time":295448,"text":"or some opportunity for an appeal."},{"time":298434,"text":"This example from another prisoner\nshows how those requests are viewed."},{"time":303241,"text":"\"Wants a transfer.\" \"Told him no.\""},{"time":307366,"text":"At one point, the prison warden himself\nrecommended McGowan's transfer"},{"time":311117,"text":"out of the CMU citing his good behavior,"},{"time":314414,"text":"but the warden was overruled"},{"time":316479,"text":"by the Bureau of Prison's\nCounterterrorism Unit,"},{"time":319717,"text":"working with the Joint Terrorism\nTask Force of the FBI."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323571,"text":"Later I found out that McGowan\nwas really sent to a CMU"},{"time":326211,"text":"not because of what he did,"},{"time":328154,"text":"but what he has said."},{"time":330149,"text":"A memo from the Counterterrorism Unit\ncited McGowan's \"anti-government beliefs.\""},{"time":336333,"text":"While imprisoned, he continued writing\nabout environmental issues,"},{"time":339868,"text":"saying that activists must\nreflect on their mistakes"},{"time":342710,"text":"and listen to each other."},{"time":344760,"text":"Now, in fairness, if you've spent\nany time at all in Washington, DC,"},{"time":348045,"text":"you know this is really a radical\nconcept for the government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352408,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":354809,"text":"I actually asked to visit\nMcGowan in the CMU."},{"time":358328,"text":"And I was approved."},{"time":360460,"text":"That came as quite a shock."},{"time":362578,"text":"First, because as I've discussed\non this stage before,"},{"time":367603,"text":"I learned that the FBI has been\nmonitoring my work."},{"time":371430,"text":"Second, because it would make me the first\nand only journalist to visit a CMU."},{"time":377189,"text":"I had even learned"},{"time":378371,"text":"through the Bureau of Prisons\nCounterterrorism Unit,"},{"time":381601,"text":"that they had been monitoring my speeches\nabout CMUs, like this one."},{"time":387128,"text":"So how could I possibly\nbe approved to visit?"},{"time":391222,"text":"A few days before I went\nout to the prison, I got an answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396471,"text":"I was allowed to visit McGowan\nas a friend, not a journalist."},{"time":400860,"text":"Journalists are not allowed here."},{"time":402972,"text":"McGowan was told by CMU officials\nthat if I asked any questions"},{"time":406541,"text":"or published any story,"},{"time":408484,"text":"that he would be punished\nfor my reporting."},{"time":412308,"text":"When I arrived for our visit,\nthe guards reminded me"},{"time":414796,"text":"that they knew who I was\nand knew about my work."},{"time":417094,"text":"And they said that if I attempted\nto interview McGowan,"},{"time":419698,"text":"the visit would be terminated."},{"time":422671,"text":"The Bureau of Prisons describes CMUs\nas \"self-contained housing units.\""},{"time":428515,"text":"But I think that's an Orwellian way\nof describing black holes."},{"time":432805,"text":"When you visit a CMU,"},{"time":433981,"text":"you go through all the security\ncheckpoints that you would expect."},{"time":437131,"text":"But then the walk\nto the visitation room is silent."},{"time":441756,"text":"When a CMU prisoner has a visit,\nthe rest of the prison is on lockdown."},{"time":447112,"text":"I was ushered into a small room,"},{"time":448962,"text":"so small my outstretched arms\ncould touch each wall."},{"time":452761,"text":"There was a grapefruit-sized\norb in the ceiling"},{"time":455580,"text":"for the visit to be live-monitored\nby the Counterterrorism Unit"},{"time":458779,"text":"in West Virginia."},{"time":460640,"text":"The unit insists that all the visits\nhave to be in English for CMU prisoners,"},{"time":465023,"text":"which is an additional hardship\nfor many of the Muslim families."},{"time":468634,"text":"There is a thick sheet of foggy,\nbulletproof glass"},{"time":472040,"text":"and on the other side was Daniel McGowan."},{"time":476104,"text":"We spoke through these handsets\nattached to the wall"},{"time":478986,"text":"and talked about books and movies."},{"time":481334,"text":"We did our best to find reasons to laugh."},{"time":484554,"text":"To fight boredom and amuse himself\nwhile in the CMU,"},{"time":487745,"text":"McGowan had been spreading a rumor\nthat I was secretly the president"},{"time":491849,"text":"of a Twilight fan club in Washington, DC"}]},{"cues":[{"time":495844,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":497836,"text":"For the record, I'm not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500209,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":501754,"text":"But I kind of the hope the FBI\nnow thinks that Bella and Edward"},{"time":505376,"text":"are terrorist code names."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507546,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":510073,"text":"During our visit, McGowan spoke most\nand at length about his niece Lily,"},{"time":516539,"text":"his wife Jenny and how torturous\nit feels to never be able to hug them,"},{"time":522687,"text":"to never be able to hold their hands."},{"time":526227,"text":"Three months after our visit, McGowan\nwas transferred out of the CMU"},{"time":529774,"text":"and then, without warning,\nhe was sent back again."},{"time":533956,"text":"I had published leaked\nCMU documents on my website"},{"time":538220,"text":"and the Counterterrorism Unit said\nthat McGowan had called his wife"},{"time":541465,"text":"and asked her to mail them."},{"time":544307,"text":"He wanted to see what the government\nwas saying about him,"},{"time":547064,"text":"and for that he was sent back to the CMU."},{"time":549982,"text":"When he was finally released\nat the end of his sentence,"},{"time":552656,"text":"his story got even more Kafkaesque."},{"time":555434,"text":"He wrote an article\nfor the Huffington Post headlined,"},{"time":557998,"text":"\"Court Documents Prove I was Sent to\na CMU for my Political Speech.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":562122,"text":"The next day he was thrown\nback in jail for his political speech."},{"time":568923,"text":"His attorneys quickly secured his release,"},{"time":570980,"text":"but the message was very clear:"},{"time":573602,"text":"Don't talk about this place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576472,"text":"Today, nine years after they were opened\nby the Bush administration,"},{"time":581089,"text":"the government is codifying\nhow and why CMUs were created."},{"time":585706,"text":"According to the Bureau of Prisons,"},{"time":587402,"text":"they are for prisoners\nwith \"inspirational significance.\""},{"time":592325,"text":"I think that is very nice way of saying\nthese are political prisons"},{"time":596553,"text":"for political prisoners."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598764,"text":"Prisoners are sent to a CMU\nbecause of their race,"},{"time":601544,"text":"their religion or their\npolitical beliefs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604770,"text":"Now, if you think that\ncharacterization is too strong,"},{"time":607615,"text":"just look at some\nof the government's own documents."},{"time":610456,"text":"When some of McGowan's mail was rejected\nby the CMU, the sender was told"},{"time":614996,"text":"it's because the letters were intended\n\"for political prisoners.\""},{"time":619410,"text":"When another prisoner, animal rights\nactivist Andy Stepanian,"},{"time":623252,"text":"was sent to a CMU, it was because of his\nanti-government and anti-corporate views."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629722,"text":"Now, I know all of this\nmay be hard to believe,"},{"time":632716,"text":"that it's happening right now,\nand in the United States."},{"time":637159,"text":"But the unknown reality\nis that the US has a dark history"},{"time":640819,"text":"of disproportionately punishing people\nbecause of their political beliefs."},{"time":645670,"text":"In the 1960s, before Marion\nwas home to the CMU,"},{"time":650140,"text":"it was home to the notorious Control Unit."},{"time":653574,"text":"Prisoners were locked down\nin solitary for 22 hours a day."},{"time":658240,"text":"The warden said the unit\nwas to \"control revolutionary attitudes.\""},{"time":664846,"text":"In the 1980s, another experiment called\nthe Lexington High Security Unit"},{"time":669817,"text":"held women connected\nto the Weather Underground,"},{"time":672269,"text":"Black Liberation and Puerto Rican\nindependent struggles."},{"time":675987,"text":"The prison radically restricted\ncommunication and used sleep deprivation,"},{"time":680257,"text":"and constant light for so-called\n\"ideological conversion.\""},{"time":685976,"text":"Those prisons were eventually shut down,\nbut only through the campaigning"},{"time":691092,"text":"of religious groups and human rights\nadvocates, like Amnesty International."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696398,"text":"Today, civil rights lawyers\nwith the Center for Constitutional Rights"},{"time":700348,"text":"are challenging CMUs in court"},{"time":702751,"text":"for depriving prisoners\nof their due process rights"},{"time":705330,"text":"and for retaliating against them"},{"time":707434,"text":"for their protected political\nand religious speech."},{"time":711296,"text":"Many of these documents would have\nnever come to light without this lawsuit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716398,"text":"The message of these groups\nand my message for you today"},{"time":721053,"text":"is that we must bear witness\nto what is being done to these prisoners."},{"time":724833,"text":"Their treatment is a reflection\nof the values held beyond prison walls."},{"time":730339,"text":"This story is not just about prisoners."},{"time":732979,"text":"It is about us."},{"time":735027,"text":"It is about our own commitment\nto human rights."},{"time":737798,"text":"It is about whether we will choose to stop\nrepeating the mistakes of our past."},{"time":743077,"text":"If we don't listen to what Father Berrigan\ndescribed as the stories of the dead,"},{"time":748133,"text":"they will soon become\nthe stories of ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750900,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752074,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":759437,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":761849,"text":"Tom Rielly: I have a couple questions."},{"time":763708,"text":"When I was in high school,\nI learned about the Bill of Rights,"},{"time":767660,"text":"the Constitution, freedom of speech,"},{"time":770580,"text":"due process and \nabout 25 other laws and rights"},{"time":775137,"text":"that seem to be violated by this."},{"time":777706,"text":"How could this possibly be happening?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":780434,"text":"Will Potter: I think that's\nthe number one question I get"},{"time":783149,"text":"throughout all of my work,"},{"time":785160,"text":"and the short answer is\nthat people don't know."},{"time":788809,"text":"I think the solution to any of these types\nof situations, any rights abuses,"},{"time":792724,"text":"are really dependent on two things."},{"time":794441,"text":"They're dependent on knowledge\nthat it's actually happening"},{"time":797261,"text":"and then a means and efficacy\nto actually make a change."},{"time":801567,"text":"And unfortunately with these prisoners,"},{"time":803988,"text":"one, people don't know\nwhat's happening at all"},{"time":806587,"text":"and then they're already\ndisenfranchised populations"},{"time":809199,"text":"who don't have access to attorneys,\nnot native English speakers."},{"time":813255,"text":"In some of these cases, they have great\nrepresentation that I mentioned,"},{"time":816689,"text":"but there's just not a public awareness\nof what's happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819775,"text":"TR: Isn't it guaranteed in prison\nthat you have right to council"},{"time":822839,"text":"or access to council?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":824404,"text":"WP: There's a tendency in our culture"},{"time":826210,"text":"to see when people have been\nconvicted of a crime,"},{"time":829344,"text":"no matter if that charge\nwas bogus or legitimate,"},{"time":831726,"text":"that whatever happens to them\nafter that is warranted."},{"time":834716,"text":"And I think that's a really damaging\nand dangerous narrative that we have,"},{"time":838234,"text":"that allows these types\nof things to happen,"},{"time":840718,"text":"as the general public just\nkind of turns a blind eye to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844145,"text":"TR: All those documents on screen\nwere all real documents, word for word,"},{"time":849105,"text":"unchanged at all, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":851178,"text":"WP: Absolutely. I've actually uploaded\nall of them to my website."},{"time":854538,"text":"It's willpotter.com/CMU and it's\na footnoted version of the talk,"},{"time":859439,"text":"so you can see the documents for yourself\nwithout the little snippets."},{"time":862781,"text":"You can see the full version."},{"time":864193,"text":"I relied overwhelmingly\non primary source documents"},{"time":867162,"text":"or on primary interviews\nwith former and current prisoners,"},{"time":870502,"text":"with people that are dealing\nwith this situation every day."},{"time":873312,"text":"And like I said, I've been\nthere myself, as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":875654,"text":"TR: You're doing courageous work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":877384,"text":"WP: Thank you very much. Thank you all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":879564,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}